	<h2>
			Park Hill Family Bike Ride		</h2>








<p>
	<img alt="" src="/images/Photos/281254_10150238098701150_5118384_n.jpg" style="float: left; margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px; "></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
	<span style="font-size:14px;">The Park Hill Family Bike Rides are free events sponsored by the Bike Depot.  This year, there will be several rides winding through the lovely streets of Park Hill led by our Bike Depot Volunteers.  The courses are generally around 4 miles long and are planned to accommodate those cyclists on the smaller and younger end of the spectrum.  Each ride will begin at 4:00pm at the Bike Depot at <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=2825+Fairfax+St.++Denver,+CO+80207&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=38.997934,-105.550567&amp;sspn=4.993723,9.876709&amp;hnear=2825+Fairfax+St,+Denver,+Colorado+80207&amp;t=m&amp;z=16" target="_blank">2825 Fairfax Street</a> and conclude at <a href="http://obliospizza.com/" target="_blank">Oblio's</a> for $5 AYCE Pizza, with a mid-ride pause for refreshments at Clementine - <a href="http://cake-crumbs.com/" target="_blank">The Cake Crumbs'</a> Cupcake Truck.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
	 </p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
	<span style="font-size:14px;">These free rides are designed to be fun, to teach bicycling safety (helmets required) and to accommodate families.  Young riders must be riding without training wheels and be accompanied by an adult.  Smaller children are welcome on “trail-a-bikes” or in bicycle trailers behind an adult.  For more information, contact Jacqui Shumway with the Park Hill Family Bike Ride Committee at 
